POLICY

Letter'Writing

The policy on letter writing is directly related. to the Mental .Health/
Mental Retardation Act of 1966 which states in.part "Every person admitted,
committed or detained in any facility shall have the right to be furnished
with writing materials and reasonable opportunity, in the discretion of the
Director, for communicating with any person outside the institution. Come
munications shall be stamed and mailed."

Policy - all reasonable efforts should be made to supply or assist

residents in communicating by letter as often as feasible. Letter writing

should be allowed during residents‘ free time or leisure time, evenings and

weekends. Requests for assistance in letter writing should be given courteous

' and helpful response on the part of employees directly concerned 3 resident

' care. All resident mail will be sent to the Administration Building to be

stamped and shall always be properly return—addressed and identified.
.Censorship of incoming mail is forbidden. Indiyidual reasons for°super—

vision of a resident's mail shall be referred to the Superintendent.

